f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Drift is best suited for B2B sales teams, demand generation, enterprise marketing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Kayako, meanwhile, shines for mid size businesses, support teams, service companies, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2015, Drift describes itself as \"Conversational AI platform for sales and customer engagement on websites.\" Kayako, established in 2001, positions itself as \"Customer service platform providing a unified view of every customer journey.\" With 14 years between them, Kayako brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Drift offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Drift** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 5.0). However, this does not mean Kayako is a poor choice — far from it. Kayako excels in its own right, particularly for mid size businesses and support teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent for b2b lead qualification, go with Drift. If good customer journey visualization matters more to you, Kayako is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
